abstract: At an event called “The People’s Summit” in Chicago, Mr. Sanders’s backers discussed their plans to carry on his message and their intentions for the general election.
snippet: At an event called “The People’s Summit” in Chicago, Mr. Sanders’s backers discussed their plans to carry on his message and their intentions for the general election.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Ethan Winnett, a 31-year-old from Waukegan, Ill., said that if Senator Bernie Sanders endorsed Hillary Clinton after his decades as a progressive champion, it would amount to nothing short of “a betrayal of all of his principles.”

abstract: Bar graphs and schoolroom animation are employed in a political action committee’s ad that proclaims “a vote for Kasich actually helps Trump.”
snippet: Bar graphs and schoolroom animation are employed in a political action committee’s ad that proclaims “a vote for Kasich actually helps Trump.”
lead_paragraph: There’s a basic reason not to vote for Gov. John Kasich, the ad proclaims: math. Through chalkboard arithmetic and some condescending narration, a new ad from the Club for Growth political action committee adds an anti-Kasich message to its anti-Trump campaign, accusing Mr. Kasich of splitting the opposition to Donald J. Trump.

abstract: Mr. Sanders defeated Hillary Clinton in Washington, Alaska and Hawaii, which held nominating contests on Saturday.
snippet: Mr. Sanders defeated Hillary Clinton in Washington, Alaska and Hawaii, which held nominating contests on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders routed Hillary Clinton in all three Democratic presidential contests on Saturday, infusing his underdog campaign with critical momentum and bolstering his argument that the race for the nomination is not a foregone conclusion.

headline_main: Tulsi Gabbard, Rising Democratic Star, Endorses Bernie Sanders

abstract: For all their flaws and fakery, the Republican candidates have squared off frequently. But Hillary Clinton and Co. have been shamefully demure.
snippet: For all their flaws and fakery, the Republican candidates have squared off frequently. But Hillary Clinton and Co. have been shamefully demure.
lead_paragraph: The Republican presidential candidates have demonstrated such an appetite for debates that if I set up nine lecterns in my living room on a weeknight around 8 p.m. and chanted “carpet bomb” and “anchor baby,” they’d probably materialize en masse, even before I had time to vacuum and put out the artichoke dip.

abstract: The debate about debates has intensified in recent weeks and has now broken out into public recriminations.
snippet: The debate about debates has intensified in recent weeks and has now broken out into public recriminations.
lead_paragraph: R.T. Rybak, the former mayor of Minneapolis and a vice chairman of the Democratic National Committee, on Thursday accused the party’s leader, Representative Debbie Wasserman Schultz, of making “flat-out not true” statements about another top party officer, questioned her political skills and said he had “serious questions” about her suitability for the job.

headline_main: Top Party Official Accuses Democratic National Chairwoman of Lying and Questions Her Leadership

abstract: Representative Tulsi Gabbard, a vice chairwoman of the Democratic National Committee, said the message had come from the office of the chairwoman, Representative Debbie Wasserman Schultz.
snippet: Representative Tulsi Gabbard, a vice chairwoman of the Democratic National Committee, said the message had come from the office of the chairwoman, Representative Debbie Wasserman Schultz.
lead_paragraph: Representative Tulsi Gabbard of Hawaii, a vice chairwoman of the Democratic National Committee, said she was disinvited from the first Democratic presidential primary debate in Nevada after she appeared on television and called for more face-offs.
